</center>
<center>
  &nbsp;
</center>
<a name="Premack"></a><b>Premack, David. Minds with and without language</b>. 
<a href="#top">Weiskrantz (1988)</a>, pp. 46-65. 
<p>
Abstract: (from the chapter) in this chapter, I will concentrate on two of the 
possible comparisons that one can make between creatures with and without language... 
I shall compare chimpanzees and young children, and also chimpanzees that have 
and have not been taught artificial language... overlapping vs concentric circles... 
effect of language training. 
