<center>
  &nbsp;
</center>
<a name="Sergent"></a><b>Sergent, Justine. Face perception and the right hemisphere</b>. 
<a href="#top">Weiskrantz (1988)</a>, pp. 108-131. 
<p>
Abstract: (from the chapter) processes underlying face perception... spatial frequency 
composition of facial representations... experimental factors contributing to 
the emergence of a right-hemisphere-dominant involvement in processing faces in 
lateral tachistoscopic studies with normal subjects... contribution of the right 
hemisphere to the processing of faces; research on normal subjects; research on 
brain-damaged patients. 
