  &nbsp;
</center>
<a name="Horn"></a><b>Horn, Gabriel. What can the bird brain tell us about thought 
without language?</b> <a href="#top">Weiskrantz (1988)</a>, pp. 279-304. 
<p>
Abstract: (from the chapter) address issues which have recurred in this symposium, 
particularly memory processes and face recognition, and will conclude by making 
some general remarks about 'thought' and 'consciousness'... recognition through 
exposure... a brain region involved in imprinting... is there a predisposition 
to respond to faces... language and thinking... thought and consciousness in humans 
and other animals. 
