</center>
<a name="Diamond"></a><b>Diamond, Adele. Differences between adult and infant 
cognition: Is the crucial variable presence or absence of language?</b> <a href="#top">Weiskrantz 
(1988)</a>, pp. 337-370. 
<p>
Abstract: (from the chapter) similarity of AB and delayed response... evidence 
linking delayed response to prefrontal cortex... results of human infants on AB; 
results with monkeys... results of human infants on delayed response; on object 
retrieval... results of monkeys on object retrieval... abilities required by AB 
and object retrieval: insights from the function subserved by the frontal lobe. 
