<a name="Thinus-Blanc"></a><b>Thinus-Blanc, Catherine. Animal spatial cognition</b>. 
<a href="#top">Weiskrantz (1988)</a>, pp. 371-395. 
<p>
Abstract: (from the chapter) consider some spatial behaviours, in animals, which 
cannot be explained (at least at present) without referring to cognitive maps, 
i.e. to an allocentrically organized representation of environmental features... 
how do we characterize spatial behaviours... adaptation as an index of spatial 
cognition... exploration: an interface between the real world and its representation... 
exploration and representations: reciprocal links. 
<center>
  &nbsp;
</center>
